Yeah!

239
00:19:57,963 --> 00:19:59,064
{\an8}Good work.

240
00:19:59,598 --> 00:20:01,767
{\an8}<i>A member of Snow Man,</i>

241
00:20:01,833 --> 00:20:03,101
{\an8}<i>Koji Mukai.</i>

242
00:20:03,168 --> 00:20:04,369
{\an8}Can you wait here?

243
00:20:04,436 --> 00:20:07,839
<i>They spent their days together
at Kansai Johnny's Jr.,</i>

244
00:20:07,906 --> 00:20:10,075
<i>a friend who aimed for the same goal.</i>

245
00:20:10,142 --> 00:20:10,976
Hey!

246
00:20:11,043 --> 00:20:11,877
Yeah!

247
00:20:11,944 --> 00:20:13,912
-Muka-chan!
-Good work!

248
00:20:13,979 --> 00:20:15,214
I came for the encore.

249
00:20:15,280 --> 00:20:16,181
Oh, seriously?

250
00:20:16,248 --> 00:20:20,485
Good work!

251
00:20:20,552 --> 00:20:23,956
Anyhow, I'm just happy for them.

252
00:20:24,022 --> 00:20:26,425
I teared up during Daigo's speech too.

253
00:20:26,491 --> 00:20:30,028
To me right now, like...

254
00:20:30,095 --> 00:20:33,899
How do you say this?
They're a presence that inspires me.

255
00:20:35,267 --> 00:20:36,535
How do I put this?

256
00:20:36,602 --> 00:20:42,107
What I kind of imagined
or what was built up here inside me

257
00:20:43,242 --> 00:20:45,010
feels like it all disappeared.

258
00:20:45,611 --> 00:20:48,213
So I'm now really empty in a good way.

259
00:20:48,814 --> 00:20:52,784
I think I'll restart from scratch
and work hard.

260
00:20:53,385 --> 00:20:54,219
Thank you.

261
00:20:54,286 --> 00:20:55,187
Thank you.

262
00:20:55,754 --> 00:20:57,422
To be honest,

263
00:20:58,690 --> 00:21:00,592
when I wrote "Time View"...

264
00:21:03,028 --> 00:21:07,833
Of course it holds the feelings
of us seven too.

265
00:21:08,734 --> 00:21:11,370
But I wrote this
so we can cry while singing it.

266
00:21:11,436 --> 00:21:13,238
Really.

267
00:21:13,305 --> 00:21:15,407
"Time View" was very nice.

268
00:21:18,510 --> 00:21:21,146
I'm glad we were able to sing it
as we cried.

269
00:21:24,082 --> 00:21:26,551
The lyrics didn't sink
into the crowd though.

270
00:21:26,618 --> 00:21:28,954
They probably couldn't make out the words.

271
00:21:29,621 --> 00:21:32,658
Since we were all bawling while singing.

272
00:21:33,358 --> 00:21:35,260
But even still,

273
00:21:37,362 --> 00:21:40,866
the fans were intently watching us
while they cried.

274
00:21:41,533 --> 00:21:43,969
So I thought,
"I'm glad I joined Johnny's."

275
00:21:47,039 --> 00:21:47,973
{\an8}<i>Next time,</i>

276
00:21:48,040 --> 00:21:51,877
{\an8}<i>the surprising feelings flooding
the debuting Naniwa Danshi.</i>

277
00:21:53,845 --> 00:21:55,180
{\an8}I'm more worried now.

278
00:21:55,247 --> 00:21:56,348
{\an8}It's contradictory.

279
00:21:56,415 --> 00:22:00,952
{\an8}I wanted to debut, so I worked
for it, but I get scared once it's final.

280
00:22:02,354 --> 00:22:06,358
{\an8}<i>What is demanded
of them grows bigger by the day.</i>

281
00:22:07,192 --> 00:22:11,096
{\an8}The picture seen after debuting
will become different, definitely.

282
00:22:11,730 --> 00:22:14,132
{\an8}<i>How does the picture look from their eyes?</i>

283
00:22:14,199 --> 00:22:16,935
